text.paragraph:
Because of possible additive effects, advise patients to exercise caution when patients are taking other sedating medications, alcohol, or other central nervous system depressants (e.g., benzodiazepines, antipsychotics, antidepressants) in combination with rasagiline or when taking concomitant medications that increase plasma levels of rasagiline (e.g., ciprofloxacin) [see


                        Warnings and Precautions (5.3)
                     ].
